race.comment: Competitive contest to close out the card with many last-start winners engaged. CRIMSON WINGS (9) didn't measure up in town on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Has since returned with a strong win over this six-furlong journey and winning jockey Magorrian sticks. Can go back-to-back to start the campaign. SIEBERT (11) broke the maiden status when resuming and will have taken some confidence from that first-up victory. Include in calculations. The well-related SHANONI (2) (half to 2xG3 winner Sadler's Lake) is a consistent conveyance who is yet to miss the top-five in seven career outings and gets 3kg weight relief with the claim. A must for the multiples. MATCHSTICKS (13) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and may earn some minor money. DIVA LAS VEGAS (5) makes some appeal from the Michael Freedman stable.
